Figure S2 - Cluster Features

cluster_palette <- c("#46B8DACC", "#EEA236BB", "#9632B8BB")
tsne_data <- read_csv("tsne_electives.csv")
## Parsed with column specification:
## cols(
##   discipline = col_character(),
##   discipline_full = col_character(),
##   disc_code = col_character(),
##   prop_matched_discipline_elective = col_double(),
##   prop_matched_program_elective = col_double(),
##   prop_ranked_discipline_elective = col_double(),
##   prop_ranked_program_elective = col_double(),
##   mean_electives_within_discipline = col_double(),
##   mean_electives_outside_discipline = col_double(),
##   mean_other_disciplines = col_double(),
##   prop_matched_3_discipline_elective = col_double(),
##   competitiveness = col_double(),
##   prop_backup = col_double(),
##   prop_unmatched = col_double(),
##   TSNE1 = col_double(),
##   TSNE2 = col_double(),
##   electives_clusters = col_double()
## )
electives_mat <- tsne_data %>% 
  dplyr::select(-c("discipline", "discipline_full", "disc_code", "prop_unmatched", "TSNE1", "TSNE2")) %>% data.matrix()
rownames(electives_mat) <- tsne_data %>% pull(disc_code)

# get dendrogram
corelectives <- electives_mat %>% t() %>% cor()
electives_dist <- as.dist((1-corelectives)/2)
electives_hc <- hclust(electives_dist, method = "complete")
# # matrix for heatmap
# electives_mat <- tsne_data %>% 
#   dplyr::select(-c(disc_code, discipline, discipline_full, TSNE1, TSNE2, electives_clusters)) %>% data.matrix
# rownames(electives_mat) <- tsne_data$disc_code

col_labels <- c("Prop Matched with \nDiscipline Elective", "Prop Matched with \nProgram Elective", 
                "Prop Ranked with \nDiscipline Elective", "Prop Ranked with \nProgram Elective",
                "Mean Electives within\nMatched Discipline", "Mean Electives outside\nMatched Discipline",
                "Mean Other Disciplines with\n Completed Electives", "Prop Matched with >=3\n Discipline Electives",
                "Competitiveness", "Frequency of\nParallel Applications", "Prop Applicants Unmatched")

# Plot the heatmap
electives_heatmap <- pheatmap(electives_mat, color = colorRampPalette(rev(brewer.pal(n = 11, name = "RdYlBu")))(100), scale = "column",
         angle_col = "45", cutree_rows = 3, cutree_cols = 4, fontsize = 12, fontsize_row = 10, fontsize_col = 9, fontsize_number = 10,
         legend = TRUE, legend_breaks = c(-3,-2,-1,0,1,2,3,3), legend_labels = c("-3","-2","-1"," 0"," 1"," 2"," 3","Z-score\n\n\n"),
         cluster_rows = electives_hc, labels_col = col_labels)

program_elective_labels <- c("prop_ranked_program_elective" = "Prop Ranked w/ Program Elective",
                          "prop_matched_program_elective" = "Prop Matched w/ Program Elective")
my_comparisons <- list( c("A", "B"), c("B", "C"), c("A", "C") )

cluster_program <- electives_clust %>%
  na.omit() %>%
  filter(year >= 2013) %>%
  dplyr::select(year, cluster, prop_ranked_program_elective, prop_matched_program_elective) %>%
  gather(key = "match_stat", value = "value", prop_ranked_program_elective, prop_matched_program_elective) %>%
  mutate(match_stat = factor(match_stat, levels = c("prop_ranked_program_elective", "prop_matched_program_elective"))) %>%
  ggplot(aes(y = value, x = cluster, fill = cluster)) +
  geom_boxplot(outlier.color = 'grey', outlier.alpha = 0.8) + 
  scale_fill_manual(values = cluster_palette) +
  facet_wrap(.~match_stat, scales = "free_y", labeller = as_labeller(program_elective_labels)) +
  xlab("") + ylab("") +
  stat_compare_means(comparisons = my_comparisons, size = 4, method = "t.test", label = "p.signif") +
  theme_pubr() +
  theme(legend.position = "none",
        strip.text.x = element_text(size = 16))

cluster_program

ggarrange(
  as.grob(electives_heatmap), 
  cluster_program + theme_pubr(),
  ncol = 1, nrow = 2, 
  heights = c(1.6,1), labels = "AUTO", font.label = list(size = 22)) +
  ggsave("paper_figures/Figure_S2_cluster_features.png", width = 14, height = 14, dpi = "retina")

Multivariate Regression

Running multiple linear regression and beta regression to see which terms are still significant. Also running stepwise BIC with all terms and all interactors to look for significant interactions influencing unmatched rates

electives <- read_csv("electives.csv")
## Parsed with column specification:
## cols(
##   year = col_double(),
##   discipline = col_character(),
##   discipline_full = col_character(),
##   disc_code = col_character(),
##   prop_unmatched = col_double(),
##   prop_backup = col_double(),
##   competitiveness = col_double(),
##   prop_matched_discipline_elective = col_double(),
##   prop_matched_program_elective = col_double(),
##   prop_ranked_discipline_elective = col_double(),
##   prop_ranked_program_elective = col_double(),
##   mean_electives_within_discipline = col_double(),
##   mean_electives_outside_discipline = col_double(),
##   discipline_vs_other_electives = col_double(),
##   mean_other_disciplines = col_double(),
##   prop_matched_3_discipline_elective = col_double()
## )
# match input from electives data
match_input <- electives %>% 
  dplyr::select(-c(year, discipline, discipline_full, disc_code)) %>% 
  na.omit()
lin <- lm(prop_unmatched ~ ., data=match_input)

summary(lin)

beta <- betareg(prop_unmatched ~ ., data = beta_input)

After running stepwise multiple regression the significant interactor terms are: competitiveness : mean_electives_within_discipline competitiveness : prop_backup We will visualize these interactions in figure S3

Figure S3

Interaction plots of: - Electives within Discipline vs Unmatched [ interactor: Competitiveness ] - Frequency of Parallel Applications vs Unmatched [ interactor: Competitiveness ]

electives_clust_since2013 <- electives_clust %>% filter(year >= 2013) %>% na.omit()

comp_quantiles <- electives_clust_since2013 %>%
  pull(competitiveness) %>% 
  quantile(., probs = c(0.33, 0.66), na.rm = TRUE)

# electives over competitiveness levels
p1 <- electives_clust_since2013 %>%
  mutate(Competitiveness = if_else(competitiveness < comp_quantiles[[1]], "Low", 
                                 if_else(competitiveness < comp_quantiles[[2]], "Med", "High"))) %>%
  mutate(Competitiveness = factor(Competitiveness, levels = c("High", "Med", "Low"))) %>% 
  na.omit() %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = mean_electives_within_discipline, y = prop_unmatched)) +
  xlab("# of Electives in Matched Discipline") + ylab("Proportion of Applicants Unmatched") +
  geom_point(aes(color = Competitiveness), size = 1.2) +
  geom_smooth(aes(color = Competitiveness), method = "lm", se = FALSE) +
  scale_color_brewer(type = "qual", palette = 6, name = "Competitiveness") +
  stat_cor(size = 3.2, label.y.npc = 0.975) +
  stat_cor(aes(color = Competitiveness), size = 3, label.y.npc = 0.925) +
  theme_pubr()


# backup over competitiveness levels
p2 <- electives_clust_since2013 %>%
  mutate(Competitiveness = if_else(competitiveness < comp_quantiles[[1]], "Low", 
                                 if_else(competitiveness < comp_quantiles[[2]], "Med", "High"))) %>%
  mutate(Competitiveness = factor(Competitiveness, levels = c("High", "Med", "Low"))) %>% 
  na.omit() %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = prop_backup, y = prop_unmatched)) +
  xlab("Frequency of Parallel Applications") + ylab("Proportion of Applicants Unmatched") +
  geom_point(aes(color = Competitiveness), size = 1.2) +
  geom_smooth(aes(color = Competitiveness), method = "lm", se = FALSE) +
  scale_color_brewer(type = "qual", palette = 6, name = "Competitiveness") +
  stat_cor(size = 3.2, label.y.npc = 0.975) +
  stat_cor(aes(color = Competitiveness), size = 3, label.y.npc = 0.925) +
  theme_pubr()


ggarrange(
  p1, p2, nrow = 1, ncol = 2, 
  labels = c("A", "B"), font.label = list(size = 22)) +
  ggsave("paper_figures/Figure_S3_interaction_plots.png", width = 16, height = 5, dpi = "retina")
